	Good Value good location - ideal choice.	We made a reservation here after taking advice from other Travellers from this site. Arriving after a 11 hour flight at midday, our quiet room over looking the court yard was ready for us. The room was not overly big, but clean and very comfortable beds, a great shower and very clean bathrooms. Nice decor and good amenities. Thoroughly recommend the Cafe Pescatore adjacent to the hotel as the food is very good. Ideally located to Fishermans wharf, the cable car, plus a supermarket across the road. Staff are friendly and helpful (they even bought us some English Tea with hot water).The wine reception is a great idea as it is nice to meet other travellers and great having access to the free Internet access in our room.	
Nov 25 2009 	Great Location - Nice (but small) Rooms - Helpless Concierge	After extensive research for our few days in San Fran, I finally selected the Tuscan Inn. It was a great choice! The location can't be beat. The rooms were bright, clean and the windows open. What I noticed most is the room (king size) was very small. It was difficult to find a spot to put two big suitcases --- to live out of for several days. So we were constantly stepping over them and around them. There is an in-room safe which is great. The room also had a small refrigerator but it was kept behind lock and key. Why? We don't know and were too busy to really care, but found it odd. Another odd thing we noticed is a majority of the room doors opened OUT into the hallway, rather than into the rooms. Ours opened inward, but we definitely noticed most opened out. Our room was very quiet and the window opened up to overlook a cute courtyard. The lobby also had several great gathering areas for meeting your party or just sitting to enjoy your book outside the room.Next door is a Safeway and a Barnes &amp; Noble bookstore. Both of which were great for stocking up either on water or grabbing coffee in the morning. The Wharf is just a short walk up the street, as is a laundry mat if needed and the stop for the Muni cars.The several gentlemen who worked the front desk in the evening were great and all were very helpful during our stay. They were also very patient in explaining directions on the map etc! The staff in the morning seemed to need another cup of coffee as they weren't excited to see us. Just a difference in personality I would assume.We did ask the Concierge, located in the lobby, a few questions one morning and realized that to be a mistake. Both of us having worked in tourism for over 14 years were very disappointed at the level of service provided by this gentleman. No suggestions of &quot;I would recommend, if you are in that part of SF then you should try to eat dinner here, here or here. Some options for sightseeing there would be X, Y, Z.&quot;It was very apparent to us that we were beneath his level of being a worthy tourist.The Room Attendants were excellent and friendly - very accommodating to our late morning departures before making up the room - and our room was always very clean with fresh towels as requested.I would stay here again.	
Nov 12 2009 	I wanted to love it but it was just okay	Based on the reviews here on TripAdvisor, I expected to love the Tuscan Inn, but I have to say I was underwhelmed. The location is good, and the overall decor is nice, but there was nothing that I can really rave about.This was our first trip to San Francisco (myself, my husband, and two teenage children) and we stayed at the Tuscan Inn for two nights -- a Saturday and Sunday. The first night we had a room on the outside perimeter of the building, facing Mason St., and the street noise was absolutely unbearable. It was not just cars and traffic (which I would understand) but screaming, yelling, honking, and all kinds of commotion -- especially at about 2am, which is when I'm assuming the local bars let out. The noise from inside the hotel was not much better. The walls were paper thin, and my son woke up in a panic at one point because he thought the voices he was hearing were INSIDE our room. We asked to be moved to a quieter room the next day, and the front desk was very accommodating (I got the feeling this happens all the time). The second room was smaller, with a very inconvenient bathroom layout, but at least it was quieter and we were able to sleep. We never tried the coffee/tea in the morning or the manager's reception in the afternoon (we were out sightseeing most of the time), though they are a nice touch. Our room rate included breakfast, which was a croissant and fruit at the on site restaurant. It was fine but, again, nothing I can rave about. Overall, it was a good location, but an average hotel with serious noise issues.	
