Jul 25 2009 	Good Location	You couldn't ask for a more convenient hotel for sight seeing in San Francisco. The bus stops outside the door; the F streetcar is a block away; the Powell-Hyde trolley car two blocks away; the wharf two blocks away. The staff are very friendly and helpful, particularly the concierges and the Manager's Reception is a nice touch. The hotel itself is very attractive. We loved the food at Cafe Pescatore - so nice when you are too tired to go far to eat. Having said all that, the room could have been better. There isn't much drawer space if you are staying long enough to unpack. I have a bad back and found the mattress soft and uncomfortable. Each day we had to leave a note asking for more towels, even though the request is on our profile. The toilet and sink are separated by a door but are operated by the same light switch so it is impossible to turn the light on in the toilet without also turning on the light in the room, an inconvenience to the partner trying to sleep! I no sooner commented on the sharp edge of the nighttables when my partner rolled over and cut his forehead - we moved them away from the bed after that. Although some reviewers have commented on noise, we found the room very quiet and never noticed noise at all.	
