Jun 1 2009 	Explore San Francisco's Best Neighborhoods	I stayed at the Tuscan Inn with my 10-year-old daughter for a special overnight &quot;mommy and me&quot; trip. Although we live in the San Francisco Bay Area, we wanted time to explore certain special neighborhoods in San Francisco best seen on foot. The Tuscan Inn was perfectly located for us to walk a few blocks in the opposite direction of the touristy Fisherman's Whaft to the traditional Italian neighborhood of North Beach. We walked through parts of Chinatown, visited City Lights Bookstore where the Beat movement took flight, shopped the boutiques along Grant Street and had a great, spontaenous dinner. The next morning we went back to a lovely neighborhood cafe on Mason Street two blocks from the hotel to enjoy homemade pastries, a latte and local characters. A highlight of our visit was the historic boats at the Hyde Street Pier -- a national Park Service site that costs only $5.00 for an adult with free entrance for shildren -- we were both fascinated for nearly two hours and it was not crowded. Our room at the Tuscan Inn was cheerful, beautifully decorated, quiet, spacious, bright, well lit for reading at night and offered an iPod port. The service was quick and gracious checking in and out. I highly recommend the Tuscan Inn as a base while in San Francisco.	
