May 23 2009 	WOW - What a great hotel	We stayed at the Tuscan Inn for four nights in mid May 2009. We were in town for the Bay to Breakers.What a wonderful spot.We had a car, so we started with the valet. He was very friendly, and explained just what we had to do to retrieve our car – when they were available (24/7), how long to expect to wait to retrieve the car ( about 7 minutes), etc. He also helped us with our bags to the front desk.The front desk staff were very friendly and efficient. Our room rate was all in order – we’d booked a TravelZoo special, and the front desk had the right rate, and the right parking discount.We asked for a high room, and off the street. We got exactly that. We went down for the free wine reception, and had a great time. We met a number of other travellers, and the wine pour-ers and hostess were very friendly and efficient. The wine reception each night became an event we looked forward to (for more than just the wine!). The wine is Charles Shaw (two buck Chuck) so you wine afficianados should not get too excited, but it was fine for our standards. The room itself was a little small - pretty normal for the wharf area. But it was immaculate and nicely decorated. The bed was big and very comfortable. One interesting thing – the room doors open out to the hallway, rather than in to the room. This makes the room seem slightly bigger, as the door does not swing into the room, taking up space. I’m surprised more hotels don’t do this. The bathroom door does the same thing, making the bathroom seem slightly larger.The room was very quiet. We'd seen some reviews saying the rooms that face the street are noisy, so by asking for a room off the street, we got a very quiet room.The air conditioning worked perfectly. Yes – we needed air conditioning in San Francisco. It was unseasonably warm when we were there.We ate in the hotel restaurant – an Italian theme – and it was very good. Good food and service.The concierge was very helpful and extremely friendly. We did find the concierge was very busy in the mornings, trying to arrange tours for people. We didn’t use the workout facility.The hotel has one computer (with printer) available with free internet. And free wi-fi throughout the hotel which worked flawlessly.This is a Best Western, but it is operated by Kimpton - so it is pet friendly. They advertised that with a picture of the manager's dog on the check in desk. All in all it was a wonderful stay and I’d highly recommend it – we did get an amazing rate, so that made it seem even better.The location is excellent if you want to be near the wharf. It was a two block walk to Pier 39. And the street it was on (North Point), was busy enough to always feel safe walking, but not so busy that you felt crowded.The only downside, is not a fault of the hotel – rather, my personal preference. We usually stay in the Marina District, but we wanted a hotel near the wharf so we could walk to the Bay to Breakers (we didn’t want to stay near Union Square, even though it would have been more convenient).I like visiting the Wharf, but personally, I’d rather stay in the Marina District, and visit the wharf. To be honest, I was pretty sick and tired of the wharf after four days. But again, that was my choice, not a hotel problem.All in all, if you want to stay near the wharf, I’d highly recommend the Tuscan Inn. Though I’d try to get a discounted rate.	
