May 3 2009 	Excellent hotel close to Fisherman's Wharf	This was the third time we have stayed at the Tuscan Inn and each time it has been excellent.The staff are very friendly and go out of their way to help you. We had a double room with 2 queen beds. Although the rooms are not huge, our room was still easily big enough for 2 adults and a child (plus 3 weeks of holiday gear). The hotel is close to Fisherman's Wharf (5 minutes walk max from the seafront) but not so close that it gets the noise. The base of the cable car line is one block away and there is a Safeways one block away as well.At 5 pm every day the hotel holds an informal reception where you can have a couple of glasses of wine and normally some food brought in from the Italian restaurant next door. After spending an exhausting day walking the hills of SF, this is a great way to unwind before heading off for a meal. In our case we used the adjacent Italian restaurant-if you are staying at the Tuscan Inn you get 10% off your bill.They've got an underground garage at the Tuscan Inn but we didn't use it, as we there is no need for a car in SF. The cable cars provide an easy way of getting around SF but the costs can soon mount up if you are using them continually. We walked much of the time and took in the views.	
