Feb 17 2009 	Great Valentines Weekend	My husband and I stayed here for Valentines weekend and just got back last night. We thought the hotel was a great value. We booked online through the hotel website and used our AAA card to get a discounted price and it was well worth it. I researched a bit before choosing to book with the Best Western. It's diagonally across from the Sheraton which was one of our options. We decided on the Best Western after we figured we'd save more and still be as close to Fisherman's wharf. Not only was it due to price, but after reading reviews and looking at pictures, the Best Western Tuscan just seemed to be more comfy and less touristy, which it was. The rooms are decorated well, not too flashy and yet still modern. Yes, the rooms aren't that big, but after deciding that our main goal was to find a nice clean hotel close to Fisherman's wharf and near a lot of the public transportation, it was a perfect choice for us. Although our weekend was during a storm, the close proximity to the piers and public transportation still made our location idea.The staff was very helpful in giving us suggestions and directions when we asked. They also scheduled our shuttle back to the SFO airport. I didn't get to take advantage of the free coffee in the morning, but my husband and I did go to the 5pm-6pm cocktail hour, which we enjoyed. It was nice to have a drink or two and talk to fellow travelers. Only complaint that we had was when we found out that there was no in-house gym. Although they didn't have a in-house gym, they did say they had passes to the 24 Hour Fitness across the street in the shopping center. Too bad it was raining pretty hard and discouraged us from going.(If you plan to stay for 2 to 3 days and are planning to take advantage of the public transportation in Downtown SF, get the 3-day MUNI pass for $18... the front desk can tell you where to get them. The hotel only offers 1 day passes for $11, which is a good deal, but if you are staying for longer, the 3-day pass is worth it... you even still save a bit if you only use it for 2-days.)	
