 thing each morning. The room has a coffee perculator and a supply of reasonable coffee was repenished daily.It is in an ideal situation to acess public transport, a short walk to the end of the street near the cruise pier is the trolley car, and another short walk the other way takes you to the cable cars. Pier 39 is close by and so are many other attractions such as the Maratime Museum, Ghiradelli Square, Fishermans Wharf, and many great vistas can be seen walking along the promenade down along the Embarcadero. I would have no hesitiation in recomending this establisment to my friends, and we would return here on any future visits to San Francisco, esp if we were cruising out of this port as it is very close to the cruise terminal.	
