Apr 22 2007 	Best ever stay at SF wharf	This is now our favorite hotel near the San Francisco Wharf. As other reviewers have said most everything is within easy walking distance. The Wharf, Safeway, Trader Joes, numerous restaurants including Burger King and Denny's, and the cable car are all a 5-10 minute walk from the hotel. We especially enjoyed eating at Cesar’s on Bay Street, which is an Italian restaurant at the same location for over 50 years.Staff was all friendly and courteous. We had a corner room with a separate sitting area. Very clean and nicely decorated. We could see Coit Tower and downtown SF from two windows, a peek at the bay from another, and the tops of Golden Gate Bridge from another. Several have mentioned the charge for parking. It really does save if you can get a deal with free parking, but the fee is not out of line. Valet parking was $36 a day, but we're not complaining because other SF wharf hotels have charged us a similar fee even without the valet service.Will definitely stay at the Tuscan Inn when we return to SF in October.	
