Jul 29 2005	Great Decision to Stay Here!	Due to the reviews on this sight, I recently stayed at the Tuscan Inn. This was a GREAT decision. I have never stayed at a Best Western before, but I think this is not your typical BW hotel! The lobby was decorated beautifully, giving you a feeling of being in a European hotel. Cocktail hour in the lobby with the fireplace burning was a delightful treat. They offered three styles of wine, Peroni beer, Pellegrino water, sodas, and a snack. Amazingly, with a 3-night stay, we made cocktail hour 3 times. You could chat with other guests, or just keep to yourselves; the atmosphere was warm and friendly. The complimentary coffee and biscotti in the morning was another hit. Their biggest challenge was keeping the coffee urns filled, as everyone seemed to enjoy the coffee.We ate at the attached Italian restaurant the first night due to exhaustion, and found it to be outstanding. This is not your typical spaghetti and meatball restaurant. The restaurant was decorated beautifully, the wait staff was professional without being snobby, the menu was creative and delicious. The tiramisu for dessert was one of the best I’ve ever had.I feared the room size because of the other reviews, but I think we got lucky and received one of their larger rooms. We requested 2 double beds for 3 women, and were expecting a closet-sized room. What we received was more than adequate. We were in the back of the hotel with a “view” of the inner courtyard, but it was quiet and we got a peaceful night’s sleep. Other guests on the street-side of the hotel were not as fortunate due to excessive street noise.The rooms were freshly and creatively decorated, and meticulously clean. The furnishings were bright and cheery (looked new), and having the one wall mirrored not only made the room feel larger, but with 3 women staying in the room, we never had to fight for mirror time. The goose-down duvets are another European touch.If I had to find one negative thing in the room (and I’m searching), it would be that the shower and toilet were in a separate room from the sink (good thing), but the light switch for the shower was tied into the same light at the sink. So, if one person wanted to shower and required the light on, it would also light up the sink area, which was in the bedroom area, hence, would disturb the other sleeping guests. The Concierge always had a friendly smile and was willing to help with any questions that came his way. The front desk and the housekeeping staff were equally as friendly.As far as parking is concerned, we were shell-shocked at what most of the hotels charge for parking—up to $40/night. The Tuscan is $29/night, but if you search for a package rate on their web site, you may get parking included in your room rate. Great value. Also, there is a public garage across the street from the hotel if you want to self-park. I don’t know what their rates are though. The hotel is in a great location; you can walk to anything in the Fisherman’s Wharf area. In fact, we even walked to Lombard Street one morning. Now that was a hike! And, conveniently, there is a Safeway and a drug store hidden in the parking garage across the street. Yes, hidden. We made several trips to the Safeway for more film, bottled water, etc. Very convenient. I highly recommend this hotel and would not hesitate to stay there again. Hope you enjoy your time their as much as we did.	
Jul 28 2005	Bella! Wonderful Hotel!	My wife and I have travelled the world and stayed in hundreds of hotels in the US, Europe and Asia. This hotel ranks among the top. The service was excellent, the room was terrific, the bed was incredibly comfortable and the hotel is centrally located to all the major attractions of San Francisco. We particularly enjoyed the complimentary wine hour that the hotel features every day from five to six. We went on two day-long tours when in San Francisco including a day in the Napa/Sonoma valleys and the company we used is just down the block from the hotel so we didn't even have to wait for the pick-up bus. I would highly recommend this hotel.	
