Jul 20 2004	Just OK	OK hotel,very small and tight room, nice lobby and good location if you want to be by all the tourists that get drawn to the wharf, the best part of the hotel- the restaurant downstairs on the corner, a little pricey but good breakfeasts and dinners. if you want to be more center city, check out other locations in a different area. Oh yeah - bring a sweatshirt sweater and warm jacket, it was pretty cold, something I would never expect for California but Mark Twain was right and according to our bus driver the best time to visit is in Sept/ Oct, when all the fog burns off and you can see the beautiful sun	
Jul 13 2004	Great Hotel	This is a great place to stay and very convenient. It's located very near the Fishermans Wharf but a few blocks away, so it's still quiet. The rooms are nice but small and ask for a room that faces the courtyard. Every afternoon at 5 wine is served and it is a nice way to relax after a day of sightseeing. The hotel has a wonderful concierge who was extremely knowledgeable and helpful.	
Jul 8 2004	Wonderful Experience!	My daughter and I stayed at the Tuscan Inn early July 2004 for two nights and loved it! The staff was friendly and helpful, the beds were comfortable, the rooms were clean, and the location was convenient. We really enjoyed the evening beer and wine receptions as it gave us an opportunity to meet other visitors and share tips for our visit! I also loved my chair massage! I would definitely stay there again and recommend it to my friends. While some have commented that the rooms are small at the Tuscan, that was not an issue for us...we were there to see the city, not hang out in our hotel rooms!	
Jul 7 2004	Awesome Experience!	We stayed there this past weekend and LOVED it! The front desk was friendly and prompt. The 24 hr. valet was fast as well. We had an ultra clean, large corner room with views of Coit Tower and the Wharf. The location was perfect for a walk to the wharf and North Beach. Morning coffee and biscotti was a nice touch as well as the all you can drink free wine hour in the evening. You will not go wrong here!	
Jun 25 2004	A great location!	We stayed at the Tuscan Inn for 2 nites in June 2004 and found it quite appealing. A superb location, reasonable price, easy access to all the main sights and transit lines to get around the city. Clean and well-appointed rooms were a bit smallish for a family of four, (we used a King, sofa bed and rollaway), but as one previous reviewer indicated, we spent most of our time out and about. Excellent staff and service and the adjoining Italian restaurant was superb. A very nice lobby. A very cheerful staff and prompt service. Highly recommended!	
