Jun 12 2004	Great hotel	We stayed here in June 2004 for 3 nights. We loved the friendly, relaxed atmosphere and the opportunity to meet fellow guests at the &quot;happy hour&quot; in the hotel lobby each evening. The location of the hotel provides easy walks to numerous area attractions. Our room was a little small but very clean and well appointed. We enjoyed our stay there so much we returned for another night before leaving the San Francisco area. Highly recommended.	
Jun 6 2004	Great Place to Stay in SF!	We stayed at the Tuscan Inn on Halloween Weekend of 2003. We had absolutely no problems whatsoever, the courtyard room we had was quiet, small and cozy. After all, who needs a huge &amp; fancy suite when you have a city like San Francisco to explore?! The location is perfect, right near the Wharf and lots of restaraunts &amp; shops. Also, it is a block away from the trolley turnaround. There was a motorcycle rental place and a bicycle rental place 5 seconds away, which we took full advantage of. The Tuscan also offered complimentary wine happy hour from 5-6pm in the warm &amp; cozy lobby where you can wind down your day and meet other hotel guests or just hang out by yourselves. We will stay there again if we ever return to San Francisco!!	
Apr 14 2004	Excellent Hotel	My husband and I stayed here in March 2004 for 4 nights en-route to Australia. This hotel is absolutely brilliant, conveniently situated within walking distance for all tourist activities, The Wharf, Pier 39, cable cars etc.The rooms are very clean, spacious and quiet (ask for a quiet room). The manager's wine reception every evening between 5 - 6pm is a must where you can meet your fellow travellers if you are so inclined.The Cafe Pescatore (adjoining) is a must if you like Italian food. The pizzas and pastas are superb, and the tirasamu is out of this world!All in all, a fantastic hotel and a great location. I would definitely recommed this place and look forward to returning in the future.	
Apr 9 2004	Loved It (But Beware The Incompetent Desk Clerk)	We stayed at the Tuscan Inn in August 2003 for 9 days. We loved the location and were able to walk to take a trolley to all of our desired local destinations. The hotel staff was great and housekeeping went so far as to organize the toiletries I had brough from home and had left scattered on the vanity. Our room decor was cute and given the small size of the room (as is the case with most SF hotel rooms), they used the space well and provided a charming and relaxing atmosphere. I am originally from the Monterey Bay area and my fiance is from Alabama. This was his first trip to CA and he fell in love and had an awesome time. The hotel restaurant is overpriced and average--I would advise venturing out. The only real problem I had was at checkout. I received my bill and paid it and was walking out the door when I noticed it was incorrect. They had overcharged me by at least $600. I turned around and went back to the front desk clerk who informed me that he could not make a correction and give me a refund but handed me a card with accounting's number on it. He advised me to call them once I returned to DC (because they were currently at lunch). Given that he couldn't understand what the error was when I was standing in front of him pointing it out. I was not about to leave and hash it out long distance over the phone. After 15 minutes of refusing to help me and telling me it was beyond his control and out of practice to make corrections at the desk, another woman (a manager?) overheard and asked what the problem was. I explained and she fixed it in 3 minutes and gave me a refund. Perhaps he was still in training or was the kind of person who liked to pretend he knew what he was doing and didn't want to ask for help. Outside of this incident, everyone else was great. Review your bill very closely!!	
Apr 5 2004	Great location nice atmosphere!	This hotel was charming and we enjoyed our stay there! The location is terrific- away from the city hassle but within walking distance to many attractions. The rooms are small but attractive. The bathrooms are quite small compared to other hotels but adequate. The staff is friendly and helpful. My only complaint is that the restaurant does not open to 7 AM and they do not offer a buffet that the other hotels offer. We wind up going to the Hyatt at the next block for a great breakfast buffet as we had to get an early start for our booked tours. The nighly wine reception is also a chance to meet others and chat!	
