Feb 26 2004	A Taste of Italy near Fisherman's Wharf	Back during the week of 9/11/01, stayed 5 days! Great Location. Close to shops &amp; Resturants @ Pier 39 &amp; Fisherman's Wharf. Also, China Town &amp; the cablecars were within walking distance. Great people, service was terrefic, (especially during this stressful time!) The morning biscotti with coffee, &amp; early afternoon wine hit the spot. Our room was very comfortable, clean &amp; cozy. Nice lobby area with fireplace, great view of gardens. Their curteous staff helped with our travel plans for tours and also assisted during check-out (while the planes were still grounded.) Teaming this Hotel with the great food &amp; service @ Cafe Pescatore, I would definitely choose this hotel again while in SF, an experience we won't ever forget.	
Feb 23 2004	Great location small rooms...	When we finally arrived at the Tuscan Inn after having the wrong address, I was disappointed to find that there was a $50 pet charge. The website had indicated that it was a pet-friendly hotel, and I had called to verify, but was never told of any charge. I was aupset, since my $89/night room had gone to $138/night between the parking ($24/night) and the pet charge. I was also disappointed that the hotel's &quot;room service&quot; came from a nearby pizzeria, but the hotel still charged a fee on each delivery. I was disappointed that while it was the most money I had ever spent on a hotel, it was also the smallest room I had ever stayed in. The clerk when I checked in was rather rude. The next morning my husband went down to the front desk to see if anyone would be a little kinder than the rude man the night before. Fortunately a female manager was there and appeased him. I was all ready to leave, despite the fact that we would have to fork over more money for our pet charge somewhere else. We ended up staying, though we now had less spending money. Being that I worked as a front desk person at a Best Western for quite awhile I was on the lookout for good service and facilities...I was not all that impressed.That said, the location is marvelous. We didn't pull our car out of the parking garage the whole time we were there. Since the sights we wanted to see were mostly around Pier 39, we were able to walk everywhere. There is also a handy 7-11 close by so one can purchase snacks and sodas for their room. Would I stay there again? Maybe, if I got a good deal, and did not bring my dog.	
Feb 19 2004	outstanding service	My wife and I spent Valentine's Day Weekend at the Tuscan. Before we left home I contacted the hotel to get a courtyard room, it's quieter, and to have roses in the room when we arrived. Yvette handled the room and because the concierge was ill, gave the numbers of some local florists. When we arrived at our room the flowers were there. On Friday, from 5-6pm they have a mangers hour with wine, beer etc. It was a time to meet new people and enjoy a good beverage. The rooms are nicely appointed with an honor bar that is not outrageously priced. The hotel is located near Fisherman's Wharf.	
