Jan 7 2004	Great Location Friendly Staff	The Tuscan Inn is in a great spot of the Harbour, Golden Gates Trips, Alcatraz and all the seals and manages to cut out the noise of the busy streets/ tourists. It is easy to get a tram into the city and there are some restaurants with great views close by.The rooms are clean and comfortable although mine (With two double beds) could have been bigger. The staff are friendly and there is one computer for internet access as well as free coffee and biscuits in the afternoon.There is no hotel bar but an italian restaurant is attached to the hotel which was nice and convenient.	
Dec 15 2003	Loved it	Stayed 9 nights at the Tuscan Inn in November 2003. Staff were friendly and helpful. Room was small, but very comfortable. The hotel and our room were kept spotlessly clean. We enjoyed the extra amenities such as newspaper, morning coffee &amp; cocoa &amp; biscotti and the evening wine receptions. We will likely try to stay at this hotel next time we come to San Francisco.	
Dec 4 2003	Nice Property	We stayed at the Tuscan Inn for 3 nights. The property was neat and clean and only 2 blocks from the Warf where all the action is. It was a very convenient location to Pier 39 and the trolley cars. The rooms were a little smaller than what I was use to but I believe that is common in San Francisco. Everyone is invited for the evening wine reception which is 1 hour long. During that time there is a very nice and knowledgable gentlemen who offers free chair massages. There are only x-amount of slots so be sure to sign up early before all spots are gone. (He gets there about 4:45pm) One of my only complaints about the property was the conceirge. Since we are tourists we had to ask him a few questions on how to get around. He wasn't very clear when he explained directions. Since we were exploring a very large city we asked if there were some areas to avoid for safety purposes. He asked where we were from and then proceeded to tell us that cops get shot there too. What kind of answer is that? We are trying to protect ourselves from any bad places and we get an idiotic answer like that. I'm sorry but we are tourists needing information, if you don't like people asking you all these questions maybe you shouldn't be performing that job anymore. The greatest help came from a very lovely desk clerk who did a great job with getting us where we needed. We asked her how to get back to the airport without having to pay the shuttle service $15 each. She suggested the bus and sub system. Then she went out of her way and pulled up the routes and planned it all out for us. Told us where we had to leave from and what time to be there. She even printed us out a schedule. I have never been on any public transportation before so I was a little nervous doing this. I felt completely safe and would not hesitate doing it again. The residents of the city were very nice and helpful. It was raining one day and we were walking out of a restaurant. There was a very nice gentleman who had a large umbrella and shared it with me. I thought that was an extremely kind gesture from a stranger.	
Nov 28 2003	Lovely Lovely Lovely	My sister and I just got back from spending two nights at The Tuscan and let me tell you, the first time was great, but the 2nd time was even better. The room was a little small for the two of us but the decor and the bed made up for it. The bed was very comfortable. We stayed in room 442. The hotel is very convenient for the trolley, bus line and a few blocks from Fisherman's Wharf. In the morning they serve in the lobby area, delightful biscotti's, coffee and tea and since it was Thansgiving, they also had a spread of pastries which normally they do not have but probably since it was a holiday they did something special. The front desk staff were more than helpful. I would highly recommend this hotel to everyone!	
