Sep 25 2003	Been there many times	We visit San Francisco about 4 times a year and always stay at the Tuscan Inn. The rooms are sometimes small, but when you're in San Francisco, you don't spend much time in it. The service is always great and the rooms very clean. Stayed in a few other hotels, but nothing compares for the price and the convenience of being close to everything.	
Sep 20 2003	Nothing special	While the Tuscan Inn is a perfectly fine place to stay on the Wharf, it's nothing special. Our room was extremely small, overlooking the courtyard (&quot;courtyard&quot; is a bit of a stretch - it's a very tiny area with a few potted plants and trees). The television was tiny and ancient. The staff was very aggressive about checking the honor bar regularly, and even incorrectly charged us for using it (this was reversed, but aggravating!). They do not sell 3-day Muni passes at the desk as stated in the hotel literature provided in the room. The concierge seemed to never be around. Hotel parking (valet-only) is now $23 a night. We stayed in the Radisson on the Wharf (just across the street) a few months ago and had a much better experience (larger room, better parking, gracious staff, helpful concierge) for about the same cost.	
Sep 9 2003	This was a GREAT hotel!	My husband and I stayed at the Best Western Tuscan Inn at Fisherman's Wharf for 3 nights in August and loved it so much that we booked for an additional 2 nights on our way back through San Francisco. We took the advice of the people who had submitted reviews on this site and we did ask for a courtyard room. We received this category of room both times and were very happy with the fact that we did not hear any street noise at all! Every evening from 5:00 - 6:00 they have complimentary wine and beer in their lobby by the fireplace. It really is a great atmosphere. The hotel is close to Fisherman's Wharf and the cable car lines. We were also able to walk to North Beach (a must do) as well as Lombard Street. The staff is wonderful to deal with and very helpful if you need directions or advice. I would definitely recommend this hotel.	
Aug 31 2003	Been there twice cause it's very comfy	This place fits the bill. Am sorry for those few noisey rooms that some folks got saddled with. NorthPoint mall [small] is right acroos the street with a Safeway store full of goodies. And the hotel is quite close to the Wharf with all of the tour boats and sea food restaraunts. The cable car is a block and a half away so this makes China town a snap. The Italian restaraunt in the hotel is very good. The complimentary beer &amp; wine every evening is a great amenity. The rooms are very clean and very well appointed. Be sure to ask for a quiet room so that some other poor bastard gets one of those! All in all I love this place. I strongly recommend the Tuscan Inn. Be sure to go see Muir Woods while you're there also. Jesus loves you and so do I. Oh, and ride the cool renovated trolley cars all around the city also as you really can smell the city this way !	
